      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in driver-ready condition, centered around the iconic S54B32 3.2L inline-six. This naturally aspirated engine features individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing, delivering a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and the factory M Variable Differential Lock. Recent mechanical upkeep includes a comprehensive valve adjustment and essential rear subframe reinforcement, ensuring structural integrity under high lateral loads. The suspension retains its factory-tuned multi-link geometry, providing the precise turn-in and feedback characteristic of the chassis. While the exterior displays minor road-wear consistent with its mileage, the mechanical vitals are sorted for the purist seeking a visceral, analog performance machine.",
